WEEK 2 ANSWERS OF COURSERA
In successful diplomacy, there is some sort of agreement and understanding reached between statesmen.
· Continuous diplomatic activities without long intervals
· Diplomates work under the norms of international law
· The conclusion must be accepted by another party or at least some sort of yes be achieved
· Its promotes peace and an acceptable solution, ends war and conflict in a peaceful manner
Reasons of failure of diplomacy:
· Agreement or consensus not reached at any point
· Continuous diplomatic boycott
· States stop practicing it
· Ends without any conclusion
· Idealistic utopia
· Demand greater share without respecting the right of the other party
· Be on wrong side of international law
